# ============================================================================
# Repo-root .gitignore for DynDisc4-ent1
# ============================================================================
# Scope: applies to the WHOLE repo, including A2A/, Legent/, ui/, DESIGN/,
# and any future subfolder. Subfolder-specific patterns still live in their
# own .gitignore files (e.g. A2A/js/.gitignore for node_modules, runtime
# artifacts, and the iter-6 SQLite sidecar).
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment files - NEVER commit real secrets
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standard Next.js / Node.js convention: gitignore .env and .env*.local at
# any depth in the repo. This covers all subfolders without requiring per-
# subfolder entries.
#
# .env.example* files are intentionally NOT ignored - they are committed as
# SANITIZED TEMPLATES so developers know which environment variables are
# required to run the project.
#
# RULE: real keys go ONLY in .env (or .env.local). NEVER paste real keys
# into .env.example or any other committed file. A leaked Gemini API key
# in A2A/js/.env.example (discovered 2026-05-25) prompted this repo-root
# .gitignore. Rotation of the leaked key is being coordinated with the
# key owner separately; this file prevents recurrence regardless.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/.env
**/.env*.local

A2A/js/src/audits/audits.sqlite-shm
A2A/js/src/audits/audits.sqlite-wal
